<page>
   <topic>TOOLBAR.OPEN Function</topic>
   <syntax>static open as toolbar(name  as C[, flagGlobal  as L])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>name </name>
         <description>The name of the toolbar.
</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name> flagGlobal </name>
         <description>Logical</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <discussion>
The TOOLBAR.OPEN() method opens the specified Toolbar_Name and returns an object pointer to the toolbar.
Limitations: Desktop applications only.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
tbar = toolbar.open("My Own Toolbar")
]]></example>
   
   <see>
      <ref>Toolbar Functions  and Methods</ref>
      <ref><![CDATA[<TOOLBAR>.CLOSE()]]></ref>
   </see>
 
</page>